summary.name: CO2 Concentration
summary.dataset_description: This dataset contains the monthly average atmospheric CO2 concentrations and adjusted CO2 concentrations from 1958 to 2020.

properties.description: The date of the recorded CO2 concentration.
The monthly average atmospheric CO2 concentration in parts per million (ppm).
The adjusted monthly average atmospheric CO2 concentration in parts per million (ppm), accounting for seasonal variations.

goals.question: What is the trend of CO2 concentration over time?
goals.visualization: line chart of Date vs CO2
goals.rationale: This visualization will show the overall trend of CO2 concentration over the years and help identify any patterns or anomalies.

goals.question: What is the distribution of adjusted CO2 concentration?
goals.rationale: This visualization will show the frequency distribution of adjusted CO2 concentration and help identify any outliers or skewness in the data.

goals.question: What is the correlation between CO2 and adjusted CO2 concentration?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of CO2 vs adjusted_CO2
goals.rationale: This visualization will show the relationship between CO2 and adjusted CO2 concentration and help identify any patterns or trends in the data.

goals.question: What is the seasonal variation in CO2 concentration?
goals.visualization: line chart of Date vs CO2 with monthly averages
goals.rationale: This visualization will show the seasonal variation in CO2 concentration and help identify any patterns or trends in the data.

goals.question: What is the rate of change in CO2 concentration?
goals.visualization: line chart of Date vs rate of change in CO2
goals.rationale: This visualization will show the rate of change in CO2 concentration over time and help identify any significant changes or trends in the data.

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Date'])]
    
    plt.plot(data['Date'], data['CO2'], label='CO2 Concentration', color='blue')
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('CO2 Concentration (ppm)')
    plt.title('What is the trend of CO2 concentration over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Date'])]
    
    plt.hist(data['adjusted_CO2'], bins=30, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='Adjusted CO2')
    plt.axvline(data['adjusted_CO2'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['adjusted_CO2'].median():.2f}")
    
    plt.xlabel('Adjusted CO2 Concentration (ppm)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of adjusted CO2 concentration?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Date'])]
    data['CO2_diff'] = data['CO2'].diff()
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 5))
    plt.plot(data['Date'], data['CO2_diff'], label='Rate of change in CO2 concentration')
    plt.axhline(data['CO2_diff'].median(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Median: {data["CO2_diff"].median():.2f}')
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Rate of change in CO2 concentration')
    plt.title('What is the rate of change in CO2 concentration?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
